  "_narrative": "**Where We Stand**\nWe're tied with everyone else at 0 points as Pool C kicks off. With #3 Kincardine as the heavy favorites and us sitting at #18 provincially, we'll need to play smart hockey to advance.\n\n**Our Next Game**\nWe face the Ennismore Eagles Friday April 10th at 9:15 AM to open our tournament. Rankings suggest we match up well against the #25 Eagles, but they'll come out hungry and anything can happen in tournament hockey.\n\n**Around the Pool**\nThe other 9:15 AM game has Kincardine taking on Windsor, where the highly-ranked Kinucks will be heavily favored. At 3:45 PM, we get Windsor while Ennismore battles Kincardine - we'll want to see some upsets there to keep the pool standings tight and give us multiple paths forward.",
  "_coaches_corner": {
    "don_cherry": "I'll tell ya, these Kanata Rangers girls are about to show the Ennismore Eagles what heart and determination look like! You kids out there watching - this is the future of hockey right here, and these young ladies are gonna battle for every inch of ice!",
    "talking_points": "**Mindset** \u2014 This is it, Rangers. First game of Provincials and we've prepared well for this moment. Let's start strong and set the tone for our entire tournament with confident, focused hockey from the opening faceoff.\n\n**Discipline** \u2014 We're starting with a clean slate at zero penalty minutes and that's exactly how we want to keep it. Stay smart, play hard but controlled, and don't give them any free power play opportunities to get momentum.\n\n**The Opponent** \u2014 Ennismore earned their spot here just like we did, and they'll come out ready to prove themselves against a higher-ranked team. Expect them to play with nothing to lose, so we need to match their intensity while executing our systems.\n\n**What We Need** \u2014 Only pool winners advance, so every single point matters from game one. Play our game, support each other, and take care of the details that have gotten us this far.",
